WHAT SUCCESS LOOKS LIKE (90 DAYS)
Target metrics: 
NRR 95% → 105% (+10pp)
Impact: 
MONTHLY_REVENUE_SAVED_FROM_CHURN +$___K
If you hit these targets, you'll be in 'Healthy' territory. 
--- 
MONITOR WEEKLY
Must-track metrics: 
CR (track to ensure it's decreasing) NRR (track to ensure it's improving) Customer feedback (are improvements working?) 
Leading indicators: 
Onboarding completion rate Time-to-value Usage metrics (activation, engagement) 
--- 
WHAT NOT TO DO
Don't: 
Scale acquisition until retention is fixed (you'll just churn faster) Ignore expansion (it's easier than new acquisition) Wait too long (retention problems compound)" 
